      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're absolutely right to pivot the narrative, but simply framing it as a \"success\" without new data won't convince the board; they need concrete proof that the engagement translates to future value. I suggest we quantify the long-term metrics—like brand sentiment shifts, search volume increases, or user-generated content volume—to create a compelling case that the current drop in sales is temporary and the audience is growing. If we can present a projected ROI model showing how this high engagement builds a loyal customer base for the next year, the board will see it as a strategic investment rather than a wasted budget. Just be prepared to back up those projections with industry benchmarks to make the argument stick.",
